                        <bindingDesc>
                            <binding>
                                <p>Leather covering over wooden boards.The leather was originally perhaps pink or red. Remains of this colour visible on <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/> and <locus from="RCI" to="RCI" scheme="other"/>. No visible decoration. Two leather straps fastened to the front cover with catch plates with pins on the back. Rustmarks on <locus from="LCI" to="LCI" scheme="other"/> and <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/> may indicate the manuscript originally had chain staples. One nail visible at bottom of <locus from="LCO" to="LCO" scheme="other"/> and one hole after a missing nale. <locus from="Spine" to="Spine" scheme="other"/>: Five raised double bands + endbands. Top, in gold: <quote xml:lang="sv">Gråbrödraklostrets kalendarium</quote>; bottom, in gold: A 21 </p>
                                <p>Bound by Kanutus Johannis, the guardian of the Stockholm House OFM (1484-92) according to Collijn, ‘Franciskanernas Bibliotek’, p. 129, no. 1.</p>
                                <p>
                                    <dimensions type="binding">
                                        <height quantity="310" unit="mm"/>
                                        <width quantity="235" unit="mm"/>
                                        <depth quantity="50" unit="mm"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </p>
                                <condition>The original leather seems to have been mounted on a newer leather binding. The original leather is extremely worn down. The front pastedown is medieval, whiel the back pastedown is modern.</condition>
                            </binding>
                        </bindingDesc>
                    </physDesc>
